snippet: The effort to extend long-term unemployment benefits suffered a setback in Washington when two separate proposals were voted down and the possibility of a bipartisan deal collapsed.
abstract: Unemployment benefits for 1.3 million of America's long-term unemployed, as well as millions more in future, are in jeopardy after Senate efforts to reach accord on legislation to revive benefits collapses in partisan finger-pointing.
lead_paragraph: The effort to extend long-term unemployment benefits suffered a setback in Washington when two separate proposals were voted down and the possibility of a bipartisan deal collapsed.

headline.main: Unemployment Extension Is Stalled, With 2 Proposals Defeated in the Senate
headline.print_headline: Unemployment Extension Is Stalled, With 2 Proposals Defeated in the Senate
